-- Italian Stocks Advance; Fiat, Mediobanca Lead FTSE MIB Benchmark Higher
-- B y   A d a m   H a i g h
-- 2010-11-09T16:43:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-09/italian-stocks-advance-fiat-mediobanca-lead-ftse-mib-benchmark-higher.html
Italy’s benchmark  FTSE MIB Index 
gained 349.50, or 1.7 percent, to 21,578.48 at the 5:30 p.m.
close in Milan, rising for a second day.  The following stocks rose or fell in the Italian equity
market today.  Fiat SpA  (F IM) gained 3.4 percent to 13.22 euros. Morgan
Stanley raised its estimates for third-quarter profit and its
forecast for 2011 earnings at the carmaker, saying they see
hidden value in Fiat.  Intesa Sanpaolo SpA  (ISP IM) climbed 1 percent to 2.49
euros. Italy’s second-biggest bank reported third-quarter
earnings that were in line with the 511 million-euro average
estimate of 16 analysts surveyed by Bloomberg.  Mediobanca SpA  (MB IM) rallied 4.4 percent to 7.66 euros.
Morgan Stanley rated the shares “overweight” in new coverage,
saying it is the only bank in Italy that it sees with improving
earnings trends.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adam Haigh in London at 
 ahaigh1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Merritt at   dmerritt1@bloomberg.net . 